s, high-precision Ly-$\\alpha$ data, and model-independent\n$Omh^2$ diagnostic estimates. Our results provide strong hints of a spontaneous\nsign switch in the cosmological constant and lead us to conjecture that the\nuniverse has transitioned from AdS vacua to dS vacua, at a redshift $z\\approx\n2.32$ and triggered the late-time acceleration, and suggests looking for such\nmechanisms in string theory constructions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Dec 2019 17:31:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 6 Mar 2020 15:02:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-27"}
