S achieve a much lower expected total travel time\nand expected total monetary cost for the users compared to the CPURR scheme,\nwithout negatively affecting the rest of the network. These results demonstrate\nthe efficiency of personalized (VOT-based) pricing-and-routing schemes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Dec 2019 13:13:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Jan 2020 20:04:51 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 19 Jun 2020 23:30:29 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 3 Feb 2021 03:00:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-01"}
