 the option to sequentially apply\nvarious blinding offsets for separate analysis steps with independent teams.\nThe subtle modification of the data allows us to modify the algorithm and to\nproduce a re-blinded data set without revealing the blinding secret. The method\nwas designed for the 2015/2016 measurement campaign of the nEDM experiment at\nthe Paul Scherrer Institute. However, it can be re-used with minor modification\nfor the follow-up experiment n2EDM, and may be suitable for comparable efforts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Dec 2019 15:59:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 5 Oct 2020 20:46:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-05"}
